WEBVTT

00:01.234 --> 00:05.004
[lively instrumental music]

00:05.006 --> 00:12.077
♪ ♪

00:35.468 --> 00:36.568
Good evening.

00:36.570 --> 00:38.404
I'm helen mirren,

00:38.406 --> 00:42.708
And you're watching
<i>documentary now!</i> Season 50.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.476
Would you believe
that every year,

00:44.478 --> 00:47.279
A small town in iceland
holds a festival

00:47.281 --> 00:50.816
Honoring american gangster
al capone?

00:50.818 --> 00:52.518
You would?

00:52.520 --> 00:53.819
Well, good for you.

00:53.821 --> 00:56.155
You're right.

00:56.157 --> 00:58.157
Please enjoy tonight's film,

00:58.159 --> 01:01.593
<i>A town, a gangster,</i>
<i>a festival.</i>

01:04.497 --> 01:09.568
[whistling]

01:12.806 --> 01:17.209
I'm making an al capone statue,

01:17.211 --> 01:19.144
Like, for--for display.

01:19.146 --> 01:22.748
I've made it for the past
seven years, at least.

01:22.750 --> 01:26.819
Here I have made, like, uh,
masks that you can wear,

01:26.821 --> 01:29.721
Really light, and you can
parade around with them.

01:29.723 --> 01:31.457
As you can see,
a policeman and gangster,

01:31.459 --> 01:34.760
The--the yin and yang
of--of--of--

01:34.762 --> 01:36.261
Of the mafia.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.264
[upbeat percussive music]

01:39.266 --> 01:46.338
♪ ♪

02:02.489 --> 02:09.561
♪ ♪

02:13.233 --> 02:16.535
(bergannson)
well, this is the most important
time of the year for us.

02:16.537 --> 02:18.604
Rest of the year,
we offer beautiful vistas

02:18.606 --> 02:20.472
And friendly service.

02:20.474 --> 02:23.408
But those things, you can get
in many other places.

02:23.410 --> 02:28.213
It is only here that you can get
the al capone festival.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.452
(all)
al capone.

02:33.454 --> 02:36.355
- Cigar.
- Cigar.

02:36.357 --> 02:37.422
And what do you do?

02:37.424 --> 02:38.457
[inhaling]

02:38.459 --> 02:40.392
[all inhaling]

02:45.431 --> 02:46.598
(woman)
what's this?

02:46.600 --> 02:47.599
Tommy gun.

02:47.601 --> 02:49.168
A tommy gun.

02:49.170 --> 02:50.169
Pkew, pkew, pkew!

02:50.171 --> 02:51.170
[sighs]

02:51.172 --> 02:52.471
Two tommy guns.

02:52.473 --> 02:53.639
Very good.

02:53.641 --> 02:54.673
He has two guns.

02:54.675 --> 02:56.375
That's very good.

02:56.377 --> 02:58.777
Yeah, beautiful.

02:58.779 --> 03:01.180
(all)
we love you, al capone!

03:01.182 --> 03:02.281
[all cheer]

03:02.283 --> 03:03.682
(man)
uh, what do you know

03:03.684 --> 03:05.484
About al capone?

03:05.486 --> 03:08.954
Uh, well, he was
a chicago gangster.

03:08.956 --> 03:12.291
Uh, fast cars, hats.

03:12.293 --> 03:13.458
Booze.

03:13.460 --> 03:15.360
[laughs]
booze.

03:15.362 --> 03:17.663
Hmm, newspapers,

03:17.665 --> 03:18.764
Speakeasy bars.

03:18.766 --> 03:19.898
- Tommy guns.
- Mm-hmm.

03:19.900 --> 03:22.768
Um, jazz.

03:22.770 --> 03:25.771
[slow jazzy music]

03:25.773 --> 03:29.408
♪ ♪

03:45.391 --> 03:48.727
Up-tempo.

03:48.729 --> 03:51.730
[upbeat music]

03:51.732 --> 03:54.967
♪ ♪

03:54.969 --> 03:57.970
[gentle music]

03:57.972 --> 04:03.475
♪ ♪

04:03.477 --> 04:07.813
(lorgenson)
in 1966, it was only four of us
at first.

04:46.352 --> 04:47.853
Yeah.

04:52.892 --> 04:53.992
Uh, 2.

04:56.062 --> 04:59.298
The al capone festival
we have here in arborg,

04:59.300 --> 05:00.766
There is al capone everywhere,

05:00.768 --> 05:02.034
And then there's a competition,

05:02.036 --> 05:04.636
And I think, uh,
that I would like

05:04.638 --> 05:06.038
To be in the competition too

05:06.040 --> 05:08.707
'cause I think
I-I-I look like--

05:09.876 --> 05:11.843
I think I look like al capone.

05:15.081 --> 05:17.416
I think here,
I look like al capone

05:17.418 --> 05:21.820
And here and the cigar,
and maybe I win.

05:21.822 --> 05:24.823
[light percussive music]

05:24.825 --> 05:29.661
♪ ♪

05:35.868 --> 05:37.569
[laughter]

05:37.571 --> 05:39.004
Show the cameraman.

05:39.006 --> 05:40.038
Yup.

05:40.040 --> 05:41.473
Uh, this is a new one,

05:41.475 --> 05:42.941
Uh, neeloofar shirazi.

05:42.943 --> 05:44.009
Yeah.

05:49.949 --> 05:51.950
- A little bit stupid-looking.
- You think?

05:51.952 --> 05:53.452
Uh...

05:55.555 --> 05:56.755
- We like that.
- Yes.

05:56.757 --> 05:58.457
Yeah? We like that.

05:58.459 --> 06:00.425
(andersson)
some of us--
some of us like that.

06:00.427 --> 06:01.493
What?

06:02.829 --> 06:04.429
If al capone is a woman,
you know...

06:04.431 --> 06:05.497
[chuckles]

06:06.833 --> 06:09.368
(karlsdottir)
I mean, why not?
[laughs]

06:09.370 --> 06:12.003
I just think that the world
is, like, ready

06:12.005 --> 06:14.373
For a female al capone.

06:19.412 --> 06:20.812
Definitely him.

06:22.782 --> 06:24.616
How he, you know, stands,

06:24.618 --> 06:27.052
And, uh, he's gaining weight
just for the competition.

06:27.054 --> 06:28.954
That's commitment.

06:28.956 --> 06:31.957
[slow percussive music]

06:31.959 --> 06:34.860
♪ ♪

06:34.862 --> 06:38.163
Yeah, I keep winning.
[chuckles]

06:38.165 --> 06:41.133
But still, it always feels
like a surprise, you know?

06:41.135 --> 06:43.135
When I first saw a picture
of him, I said to my wife,

06:43.137 --> 06:45.504
You know, "don't I look
like him, huh?"

06:45.506 --> 06:47.005
Yeah.

06:47.007 --> 06:50.542
People say, "oh, look out.
There's al capone."

06:50.544 --> 06:53.512
He waves at them
like he doesn't like it,

06:53.514 --> 06:55.847
But, um, he likes it.

06:55.849 --> 06:57.849
Yeah, gunnar, he's really good.

06:57.851 --> 06:59.451
I mean, he is really good.

06:59.453 --> 07:01.686
He--he looks a little bit
like him.

07:01.688 --> 07:03.889
Gunnar is--
sometimes looks like him.

07:03.891 --> 07:06.158
Sometimes he doesn't
look like him.

07:06.160 --> 07:09.428
I think it's more than just
that I have his face.

07:09.430 --> 07:12.097
Uh, I feel I have his essence,
you know.

07:12.099 --> 07:14.433
That's why I win every year.

07:14.435 --> 07:15.500
- Gunnar.
- Gunnar.

07:15.502 --> 07:16.601
- Neeloofar.
- And nina.

07:16.603 --> 07:17.736
- Nina?
- Nina.

07:17.738 --> 07:18.804
- Nina.
- Really?

07:18.806 --> 07:19.871
Yeah.

07:19.873 --> 07:21.506
(andersson)
yeah, okay.

07:21.508 --> 07:23.875
- These three?
- Yeah.

07:23.877 --> 07:26.511
All right, good work, everybody.
These are the finalists.

07:26.513 --> 07:27.579
[applause]

07:30.000 --> 07:33.002
[bright music]

07:33.004 --> 07:38.842
♪ ♪

07:38.844 --> 07:39.876
[air hissing]

07:39.878 --> 07:46.950
♪ ♪

07:57.261 --> 07:59.863
This is not really
al capone's car,

07:59.865 --> 08:03.099
But in our imagination,
it is his car.

08:03.101 --> 08:06.002
You know, last year, it was, uh,
a completely different car.

08:06.004 --> 08:07.537
That's all right.

08:11.776 --> 08:14.377
He's, uh--he's old--
old guy driving the car.

08:14.379 --> 08:16.312
You know, old people,
you know, uh--

08:16.314 --> 08:17.347
[laughs]

08:17.349 --> 08:19.182
Old people and traffic--ah!

08:19.184 --> 08:21.050
[laughs]

08:21.052 --> 08:25.388
[sprightly music]

08:25.390 --> 08:28.158
(brekke)
we are very happy
to be the only place

08:28.160 --> 08:31.528
That makes official
deep-dish pizza

08:31.530 --> 08:33.296
In the chicago style.

08:33.298 --> 08:35.431
I visited chicago
a few years ago,

08:35.433 --> 08:37.366
Uh, to see how this was made.

08:37.369 --> 08:42.005
Eh, it requires a very special
deep-dish pan to make.

08:42.006 --> 08:43.940
So I bought these pans.

08:43.942 --> 08:45.408
I brought them home with me.

08:45.410 --> 08:49.846
This is authentic
gangster pizza.

08:51.448 --> 08:52.448
Have a nice day.

08:52.450 --> 08:54.551
Deep pan pizzas for you,

08:54.553 --> 08:57.320
For everybody, my friends!

08:57.322 --> 08:59.122
Have a nice day!

08:59.124 --> 09:02.125
[upbeat music]

09:02.127 --> 09:09.199
♪ ♪

09:11.302 --> 09:13.002
Al capone!

09:13.004 --> 09:15.471
♪ ♪

09:15.473 --> 09:19.876
[indistinct chatter]

09:19.878 --> 09:22.612
(bergannson)
important year? Ah, yes.

09:22.614 --> 09:26.616
All of our years are important,
but we are at crisis.

09:26.618 --> 09:30.253
The town of vogar has decided
to have a jimi hendrix festival

09:30.255 --> 09:32.622
Exactly the same weekend
as ours.

09:32.624 --> 09:35.625
[sparse piano music]

09:35.627 --> 09:39.095
♪ ♪

09:39.097 --> 09:42.232
It is at times like this
that we sure miss

09:42.234 --> 09:45.201
Our mayor ragnarsson

09:45.203 --> 09:46.469
And his support.

09:46.471 --> 09:53.543
♪ ♪

10:04.588 --> 10:06.089
(man)
how do you feel about judging

10:06.091 --> 10:07.957
The look-alike competition
this year?

10:07.959 --> 10:09.626
It's not appealing to me,

10:09.628 --> 10:14.898
But steig, he thinks it's
really important that I do it.

10:14.900 --> 10:17.166
(man)
now, why--why is this?

10:17.168 --> 10:21.170
It's really important
for the town.

10:23.173 --> 10:26.175
[lively music]

10:26.177 --> 10:31.247
♪ ♪

10:35.552 --> 10:36.920
Uh, the gangs--

10:36.922 --> 10:39.155
Uh, junior forty thieves,

10:39.157 --> 10:41.024
Uh, bowery boys,

10:41.026 --> 10:42.525
Brooklyn rippers,

10:42.527 --> 10:46.195
Uh, five points gang.

10:46.197 --> 10:48.464
Yes. Yes.

10:48.466 --> 10:49.499
Where was his family from?

10:49.501 --> 10:50.967
I looked--

10:50.969 --> 10:52.001
Oh, I looked at the card,

10:52.003 --> 10:53.369
But it's from "sickily"--

10:53.371 --> 10:54.504
"sicilay"--sicily.

10:54.506 --> 10:56.039
Sicily, yes.
"sickily."

10:56.041 --> 10:57.540
Sicily.

10:57.542 --> 10:59.575
We like to play around
with words in iceland, yes.

10:59.577 --> 11:00.576
Yes.

11:00.578 --> 11:01.711
Sicily.

11:01.713 --> 11:03.046
Yeah, no,
he was not a sissy.

11:03.048 --> 11:04.414
- No, no.
- No.

11:04.416 --> 11:06.416
Last time, I dressed up
in al capone's suit,

11:06.418 --> 11:08.284
Like, 'cause we were
practicing,

11:08.286 --> 11:09.519
And remember when you--

11:09.521 --> 11:11.988
Yeah, I-I-I dressed
as the mistress.

11:11.990 --> 11:12.989
[both laugh]

11:12.991 --> 11:14.324
Just to have a--

11:14.326 --> 11:15.959
Because it was strange
if it was two men.

11:15.961 --> 11:17.293
- Yeah.
- Like, al capone and--and--

11:17.295 --> 11:18.294
We didn't know.

11:18.296 --> 11:19.329
And we, like, went--

11:19.331 --> 11:20.530
So...

11:20.532 --> 11:22.265
Went out to dinner
and everything in it,

11:22.267 --> 11:24.000
And it was--
it was a really good night.

11:24.002 --> 11:27.403
Yeah, we were the talk
of the town for a few months.

11:27.405 --> 11:28.671
[laughs]

11:28.673 --> 11:30.406
After ten years, I know more
about al capone

11:30.408 --> 11:32.208
Than al capone knew
about himself.

11:32.210 --> 11:35.445
So no, I'm not worried
about the trivia questions.

11:35.447 --> 11:36.713
It's all up here.

11:36.715 --> 11:40.016
I'll have a southside.

11:40.018 --> 11:41.584
Al capone's drink of choice.

11:41.586 --> 11:43.720
[chuckles]

11:43.722 --> 11:45.521
I'll have a beer.

11:48.527 --> 11:51.529
[dramatic jazzy piano music]

11:51.531 --> 11:58.603
♪ ♪

12:16.022 --> 12:19.657
"sicago," "sicago."

12:19.659 --> 12:21.026
Jazz.

12:21.028 --> 12:28.099
♪ ♪

12:36.709 --> 12:39.744
You dirty rat.

12:39.746 --> 12:41.546
Chicago.

12:41.548 --> 12:43.248
Gangster.

12:43.250 --> 12:46.117
I'm scarface.

12:46.119 --> 12:47.318
Are you hungry?

12:47.320 --> 12:48.820
Alcatraz.

12:48.822 --> 12:51.589
[sighs]

12:51.591 --> 12:53.324
Yeah.

12:53.326 --> 12:54.526
[laughs]

12:54.528 --> 12:57.228
- Hi. Hi.
- Wow.

12:57.230 --> 12:58.563
Ah, this is--

12:58.565 --> 13:00.231
You look really--
really beautiful.

13:00.233 --> 13:02.233
One--one--one--one picture
for the album.

13:02.235 --> 13:03.234
Yeah.

13:03.236 --> 13:04.769
Ah, be gangstery-like.

13:04.771 --> 13:06.604
Ah!
Nice.

13:18.851 --> 13:21.319
It's a--
it's a tommy gun.

13:21.321 --> 13:22.654
[imitating gunfire]

13:22.656 --> 13:26.091
[groaning]

13:26.093 --> 13:28.326
Die!

13:35.568 --> 13:37.769
[laughs]

13:37.771 --> 13:39.304
Okay, come on.

13:47.513 --> 13:48.746
Hold on.
Hold on.

14:06.565 --> 14:08.299
Yeah.
[clears throat]

14:15.608 --> 14:18.610
[upbeat jazzy music]

14:18.612 --> 14:23.615
♪ ♪

14:23.617 --> 14:25.150
[knocking]

14:30.656 --> 14:37.729
♪ ♪

14:38.597 --> 14:40.431
A few years ago, it struck me

14:40.433 --> 14:42.600
That, uh, we were celebrating
the life

14:42.602 --> 14:45.336
Of a man who died from syphilis,

14:45.338 --> 14:47.939
So I thought to myself,
"what better time

14:47.941 --> 14:49.674
"to educate the town

14:49.676 --> 14:53.578
On the prevention
of this kind of a disease?"

14:53.580 --> 14:54.913
So, uh...

14:54.915 --> 14:56.381
[laughs]

14:56.383 --> 14:57.615
Thanks, al.

14:57.617 --> 14:58.850
Ah, you need one.
[chuckles]

14:58.852 --> 15:01.586
Take...

15:01.588 --> 15:02.887
Yes.

15:04.490 --> 15:06.824
[crowd cheering and yelling]

15:06.826 --> 15:08.860
[whistle trills]

15:08.862 --> 15:12.430
[crowd cheering]

15:12.432 --> 15:14.232
[crowd groans]

15:14.234 --> 15:15.800
[bleep]!

15:15.802 --> 15:17.669
[groans]

15:17.671 --> 15:20.605
[cheers and applause]

15:20.607 --> 15:27.679
♪ ♪

15:34.987 --> 15:37.655
This has already been
a very successful year.

15:37.657 --> 15:40.225
I just met a couple that came
all the way from reykjavík.

15:40.227 --> 15:42.560
And--and the fact that they came
all the way from the capital

15:42.562 --> 15:45.930
To the festival speaks volumes
about its importance.

15:45.932 --> 15:48.866
♪ ♪

15:48.868 --> 15:51.936
[cheers and applause]

15:59.712 --> 16:01.913
[cheers and applause]

16:01.915 --> 16:03.548
(man)
gunnar!

16:03.550 --> 16:06.618
[laughter]

16:08.921 --> 16:11.422
(narfadottir)
okay, the next question.

16:11.424 --> 16:14.659
Gunnar, please give me the date

16:14.661 --> 16:18.730
Of the st. Valentine's day
massacre.

16:20.399 --> 16:22.900
It was on valentine's day.

16:22.902 --> 16:24.736
[laughter and cheers]

16:24.738 --> 16:26.904
(narfadottir)
the year, please.

16:30.609 --> 16:32.443
It was, uh,

16:32.445 --> 16:36.047
192...6?

16:38.384 --> 16:40.385
Uh, I'm sorry, no.

16:40.387 --> 16:41.486
[crowd groans]

16:41.488 --> 16:44.022
Uh, nina?

16:44.024 --> 16:47.558
Uh, it--
1929?

16:47.560 --> 16:48.926
That's correct!

16:48.928 --> 16:51.462
Yes!

16:51.464 --> 16:53.865
(narfadottir)
neeloofar, in which cemetery--

16:53.867 --> 16:55.333
Mount--mount--mount--

16:55.335 --> 16:57.769
Mount carmel
in hillside, illinois.

16:57.771 --> 16:58.770
[cheers and applause]

16:58.772 --> 17:00.538
That's correct.

17:00.540 --> 17:03.541
[slow percussive music]

17:03.543 --> 17:07.679
♪ ♪

17:07.681 --> 17:09.646
I really hope
that my friend gunnar wins,

17:09.648 --> 17:13.718
But if not, then it's okay.

17:13.720 --> 17:16.788
♪ ♪

17:19.892 --> 17:22.727
(man)
who do you think the, uh--
the judges are going to choose?

17:22.729 --> 17:23.861
Oh, I don't know.

17:23.863 --> 17:25.029
I think maybe--

17:25.031 --> 17:26.531
Maybe me.

17:26.532 --> 17:27.665
I don't know.

17:27.666 --> 17:29.100
But I'm too nervous to talk.

17:29.102 --> 17:30.868
[laughs]

17:30.870 --> 17:33.805
You have to--you have
to talk to me after.

17:33.807 --> 17:35.640
Please, I want to win.

17:35.642 --> 17:37.675
(brynjarsson)
no, I did not do well
in the trivia.

17:37.677 --> 17:39.444
You're not allowed
to have props onstage,

17:39.446 --> 17:41.879
And then nina brings on a--
on a wooden gun, you know.

17:41.881 --> 17:44.482
But, uh, they're taking
a lot of time.

17:44.484 --> 17:46.017
I don't know why.

17:46.019 --> 17:49.053
It's a little bit scary,
but, uh, hopefully maybe.

17:49.055 --> 17:50.988
(man)
who do you think should win
the competition?

17:50.990 --> 17:53.591
I think it's time for a woman
to win this contest,

17:53.593 --> 17:55.426
So I am rooting for nina.

17:55.428 --> 17:57.929
It has to be gunnar.
Yes, gunnar is al capone.

17:57.931 --> 17:59.931
For me, neeloofar
would be worrisome.

17:59.933 --> 18:03.634
If someone that's not from here
is al capone,

18:03.636 --> 18:06.904
I mean, what would that say
about us?

18:06.906 --> 18:09.807
It says we are open-minded
and welcoming.

18:09.809 --> 18:12.510
And neeloofar pays his taxes,
so he's just as much

18:12.512 --> 18:14.746
A part of this town
as you or I.

18:14.748 --> 18:15.913
Yeah.

18:15.915 --> 18:17.915
Yeah, that's a good point.

18:17.917 --> 18:19.784
I-I take back
what I said.

18:19.786 --> 18:21.486
Trond always admits
when he's wrong.

18:21.488 --> 18:22.987
That's what I like
about him.

18:22.989 --> 18:25.056
Welcome to the judgment
of the winner

18:25.058 --> 18:27.792
Of the al capone look-alike
competition.

18:27.794 --> 18:30.027
[cheers and applause]

18:30.029 --> 18:32.497
We have decided that this year,

18:32.499 --> 18:36.934
In a true icelandic tradition
of peace and calmness,

18:36.936 --> 18:39.036
That the winner is...

18:39.038 --> 18:42.039
[suspenseful music]

18:42.041 --> 18:46.544
♪ ♪

18:46.546 --> 18:48.846
All three entrants!

18:48.848 --> 18:50.982
[cheers and applause]

18:50.984 --> 18:53.117
Gunnar brynjarsson,
nina karlsdottir,

18:53.119 --> 18:55.086
And neeloofar shirazi!

18:55.088 --> 18:57.422
[cheers and applause]

18:57.424 --> 19:00.458
Um, we actually have
a very special guest

19:00.460 --> 19:03.928
To present the cup this year.

19:03.930 --> 19:08.466
Ah, please give
a very warm welcome to--

19:08.468 --> 19:12.737
To the great-great-granddaughter
of al capone!

19:12.739 --> 19:15.807
[cheers and applause]

19:20.078 --> 19:21.746
Oh, wow.

19:21.748 --> 19:23.981
Hey, how's it goin', iceland?

19:23.983 --> 19:26.984
[cheers and applause]

19:26.986 --> 19:28.853
My name is anne severino,

19:28.855 --> 19:30.888
And I'm from chicago, illinois.

19:30.890 --> 19:33.057
So a guy sent me a message,

19:33.059 --> 19:35.026
And, honestly,
I thought it was a prank,

19:35.028 --> 19:38.062
And now I guess I'm here
and it's all real.

19:38.064 --> 19:39.797
It's like being in outer space

19:39.799 --> 19:42.099
But outer space
is a tiny little house

19:42.101 --> 19:45.136
And, uh, people
are eating horses in it.

19:45.138 --> 19:46.904
I-I mean, he killed
so many people,

19:46.906 --> 19:49.073
So to see you guys
having so much fun...

19:49.075 --> 19:50.141
[laughter]

19:50.143 --> 19:51.242
I love that.

19:51.244 --> 19:53.911
So, uh, here you go,
you guys.

19:53.913 --> 19:55.913
All right!

19:55.915 --> 19:57.815
Give it up!

19:57.817 --> 20:00.818
[lively music]

20:00.820 --> 20:07.892
♪ ♪

20:10.028 --> 20:11.963
(karlsdottir)
now that I am al capone,

20:11.965 --> 20:12.997
I will tell him what to do.

20:12.999 --> 20:14.599
No, no.

20:14.601 --> 20:16.634
She already tells me what to do
every time.

20:16.636 --> 20:17.835
[laughs]

20:17.837 --> 20:19.070
Yeah, what he's saying
is not a joke.

20:19.072 --> 20:20.638
"wake up!"
I wake up.

20:20.640 --> 20:21.639
[both laugh]

20:21.641 --> 20:24.642
[upbeat percussive music]

20:24.644 --> 20:28.012
♪ ♪

20:30.682 --> 20:32.283
In the end, simply because
I didn't care.

20:32.285 --> 20:35.686
But then I saw
that they cared deeply,

20:35.688 --> 20:38.089
And who am I
to break someone's heart?

20:38.091 --> 20:40.157
This is not what a mayor does.

20:40.159 --> 20:46.297
♪ ♪

20:49.001 --> 20:50.735
It--it is the same,
the same honor.

20:50.737 --> 20:52.803
But it was wonderful anyway.

20:52.805 --> 20:54.171
Yeah, yeah, it's--it's fun.

20:54.173 --> 20:55.273
It was very much fun,
and--

20:55.275 --> 20:56.707
It's always fun.

20:56.709 --> 20:58.242
Even though you shared
the prize, it was--

20:58.244 --> 20:59.944
Yeah, but that's still
the same honor, though.

20:59.946 --> 21:03.314
♪ ♪

21:03.316 --> 21:06.183
I'm very proud to be looking
like al capone.

21:06.185 --> 21:07.718
Now I feel accepted.

21:07.720 --> 21:12.023
[laughing]

21:12.025 --> 21:13.257
No.

21:13.259 --> 21:20.331
♪ ♪

21:27.172 --> 21:30.608
(all)
we love you, al capone!
